STREPTOCOCCUS, GROUP A, SCARLET FEVER - UK (07): (ENGLAND)
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 6 Jul 2016
Source: Lincolnshire Echo [edited]
http://www.lincolnshireecho.co.uk/scarlet-fever-alert-twelve-new-cases-in-lincolnshire-in-just-a-week/story-29484899-detail/story.html


Health officials have revealed that 12 new cases of scarlet fever have been
diagnosed in Lincolnshire - despite the peak season having passed.

Latest figures from Public Health England show there were 4 new cases in North Kesteven last week. And there were 3 in East Lindsey, 2 in South Kesteven and 1 each in Lincoln, West Lindsey and Boston.

[Byline: CJ Hall]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As of 27 Mar 2016, Public Health England (PHE) reported a total of 10 570 cases of scarlet fever since the season began in September 2015. An increase in invasive disease caused by the same bacterium group A streptococcus (GAS) which causes scarlet fever has also been seen in England with a total of 593 cases of invasive GAS infection, such and bloodstream infection or pneumonia, reported for 2016 compared to 440 cases for the same period last year (Jan to Mar 2015).

PHE reported that this is the third year in a row in which elevated scarlet fever activity has been noted. A total of 15 637 notifications were made in England and Wales in 2014, rising to 17 590 in 2015. Weekly activity from Jan to Mar 2016 was similar or slightly above for that last year (2015)

For details see: https://www.gov.uk/government/news/update-on-rising-scarlet-fever-across-england.

Lincolnshire is an historical county on the east coast of England and borders Norfolk to the southeast, Cambridgeshire to the south and the East Riding of Yorkshire to the north https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lincolnshire. Maps of England can be seen at http://www.picturesofengland.com/images/mapofengland/england-counties.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4333149,279. - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4333149,279.]
